.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2024" "Version 1.0" "simple_shell Manual"

.SH NAME
\fBSimple_shell\fP \- A simple Unix command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B - ./hsh
.br
.B - echo \(dqyour_command\(dq | ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBSimple_shell\fP is a simple command line interpreter that allows the user to execute system commands.
.br
It supports built-in commands such as \fB"exit"\fP and \fB"env"\fP, as well as execution of external
commands.

When \fBsimple_shell\fP is launched, it displays a command prompt where the user can enter commands.
.br
After entering a command, the user can press the \fB"Enter"\fP key to execute the command. \fBsimple_shell\fP
will then process the command, executing built-in commands or external commands, and
then display the command prompt again to allow the user to enter a new command.

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
This program has no command-line options.

.SH COMMANDS
.PP
The following commands are available in \fBsimple_shell\fP:

.TP
.B \fBexit\fP :
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B \fBenv\fP :
Display the system environment.

